### P7 — Node role / config templates

**Why P7**: clustervisor ships a small library of YAML node templates
(`templates/1.1/node/{compute,login,head,storage}.yml`) so an operator can
say "this node is a compute node, give it the standard compute configuration"
without rewriting the config from scratch each time. clustr has image roles
in the DB but no template library at the config layer.

**Recommendation**:

- Add `internal/templates/node/` with embedded YAML templates, mirroring
  clustervisor's role set.
- Each template specifies: image role (already exists), default node group,
  default sudoers entries, default mount points, default tuned profile,
  default LDAP membership.
- New API: `POST /api/v1/nodes/{id}/apply-template/{name}`.
- UI: "Apply role template…" action in the node sheet.

**Time estimate**: 2 weeks.

