### Recommended UI work (prioritised)

These ride on top of the original P0–P7. They are mostly **frontend-only**
once the corresponding backend exists.

#### UP1 — Per-node sensor + SEL + console panels

Triggered by P1 (stats agent) + P5 (CLI parity for `ipmi sel`/`ipmi sensors`).
Add to the node detail Sheet three new tabs: **Sensors**, **Event Log**,
**Console**. Sensors uses a small chart library (consider `recharts` —
bundle-friendlier than ApexCharts) for live values + thresholds. Event Log
is a virtualized list with level filter + regex search + head/tail. Console
is an `xterm.js` terminal connected to a server-brokered SSH/SOL WebSocket.

**Time estimate**: 2–3 weeks for Sensors + Event Log + console (assumes
backend endpoints land first via P0/P5).

#### UP2 — Cluster dashboard

Add a top-level **Dashboard** route. Composable widget grid with three
widget kinds initially: stat-gauge, stat-graph, count. Operators pick
metrics from the new `node_stats` table (P1) and pin views per-role. Use
`react-grid-layout` for drag-and-drop. Persist layout JSON in a new
`user_dashboards` table. No Monaco / no Apex — a 200-KB widget kit beats
the 6-MB clustervisor approach.

**Time estimate**: 3–4 weeks (depends on P1 stats backend).

#### UP3 — In-browser KVM/IPMI SOL console viewer

Embed `noVNC` or `xterm.js` over a WebSocket to a server-brokered IPMI SOL
session. Shape the page like clustervisor's `console.html` — a separate
React route the operator can pop out into its own browser window. Server
side: extend `internal/image/shell.ShellManager` patterns to broker IPMI
SOL streams (`ipmitool sol activate`).

**Time estimate**: 2 weeks for SOL only; +2 weeks if KVM (noVNC) is added.
Most HPC operators only need SOL.

#### UP4 — Rack layout / datacenter view

DB additions: `racks(id, name, height_u)` and `node_rack_position(node_id,
rack_id, slot_u, height_u)` (082-style migration). Web: drag-and-drop rack
diagram (a single SVG component) on a new "Datacenter" route. Bulk power
ops feel natural here — select a rack, power-cycle all U-positions in one
action.

**Time estimate**: 2 weeks (visualisation) + 1 week (bulk power wiring).

#### UP5 — Alerts UI

Triggered by P1 (alerting engine). New top-level **Alerts** route with
Active / Silenced / History tabs, per-rule drill-down, in-line "Silence for
1h / 4h / 24h / forever" actions, and a YAML rule editor (use a tiny
syntax-highlighter — `react-simple-code-editor` + `prismjs` — not Monaco).

**Time estimate**: 2 weeks (assumes P1 alerts backend).

#### UP6 — Slurm jobs / partitions UI

Pull from `slurmrestd` (already a dependency through Slurm bundling).
New tab on the **Slurm** route: **Jobs** (current + history), **Partitions**
(state + node assignments), **Reservations**. Reuse the TanStack Query
infra. No charting needed — tables only for v1.

**Time estimate**: 2 weeks.

#### UP7 — Per-node SSH key management UI

Triggered by P5 (`clustr sshkey` CLI). On the node detail Sheet add an
"Authorized Keys" tab: list, add (paste / generate), remove by fingerprint,
fix-perms button. Backed by the same write path that clientd applies on the
host.

**Time estimate**: 1 week.

#### UP8 — Distro catalog + image library polish

Curated distro catalog in the **Images** tab: a left-rail list of vetted
upstream URLs (Rocky / RHEL / AlmaLinux / Ubuntu / Debian) for each EL
major. One-click "Pull this distro" instead of pasting URLs. Surface the
existing `BaseImage.Status` lifecycle (building → ready → failed) with a
proper status pill + "View build log" drawer (the build log SSE stream
already exists at `/api/v1/images/{id}/build-progress/stream`).

**Time estimate**: 1.5 weeks.

#### UP9 — Two-stage commit UI

Triggered by P4 (pending-changes backend). Persistent **Pending Changes**
button in the AppShell top bar with a counter badge. Click → drawer with
diff per change, "Apply All", "Discard All", "Apply Selected".

**Time estimate**: 1 week.

#### UP10 — Persistent notification drawer + saved views

Top-bar bell icon → drawer of long-lived notifications (audit events, alert
state changes, deploy completions, build failures). Save-as-view on every
filterable list (nodes, images, groups, activity). Persist views in
`user_views` table.

**Time estimate**: 1.5 weeks.

#### UP11 — Plugin / extension surfacing

Triggered by P1's plugin-pattern stats agent. **Plugins** page shows
installed stat plugins, their version, the metrics they emit, last-collection
timestamp, and a "Disable" toggle.

**Time estimate**: 0.5 week (mostly readonly view).

### What clustr's UI already does better

Worth being explicit, so the team doesn't regress on the way to UI parity:

1. **One-binary, embedded UI** with a single auth model. Cockpit auth + the
   clustervisor in-bundle auth ("Clustervisor GUI", "Connected to ClusterVisor
   server") is two layers; clustr is one.
2. **Modern stack** (React 19, TanStack Query, Tailwind v4, shadcn/Radix).
   Cockpit is on PatternFly 4 + jQuery-era plugins; the bundle ships
   "Microsoft Internet Explorer" detection strings.
3. **First-class PI / Director portal** — not present in cockpit-clustervisor
   at all.
4. **Resumable TUS uploads in-UI** for large ISOs.
5. **In-image edit shell** (PTY into chrooted writable image, WebSocket to
   browser) — clustervisor has the host File Manager but no equivalent
   image-editing flow.
6. **Command palette** (Cmd-K via `CommandPalette` component) — clustervisor
   ships PatternFly's `CommandCenter` strings but uses them differently.
7. **Audit log + API key UI** as first-class admin surfaces.
8. **No license / no ACT support funnel** — simpler operator experience.

